    communityDescription: 'Lakewood is defined by its lakes. American Lake, Gravelly Lake, Lake Steilacoom, Lake Louise, and Waughop Lake are all glacial kettle lakes formed when ice blocks melted 13,000 years ago. Fort Steilacoom Park\'s 340 acres of rolling meadows, the diverse International District along South Tacoma Way, and the community\'s connection to Joint Base Lewis-McChord give Lakewood a character that blends natural beauty with military pride and cultural diversity.',
