    localTip: 'Duvall\'s floodplain soil is so rich and moisture-retentive that moles stay shallow year-round — even in summer when upland moles tunnel deeper. If you see moles slowing down in July or August, they\'re not leaving — they\'re just in the cooler, deeper layer of your extraordinary soil.',
