    communityDescription: 'Carnation sits where the Tolt River meets the Snoqualmie River, a farming town that earned the nickname "Home of the Contented Cows" for its dairy heritage. Tolt-MacDonald Park\'s 574 acres, the annual Fourth of July celebration, and the valley\'s agricultural character keep it rooted.',
