    communityDescription: 'Mukilteo is a waterfront city with a lighthouse, a ferry to Whidbey Island, and neighborhoods that feel more like a small town than a Seattle suburb. The historic Mukilteo Lighthouse at the state beach park is the city\'s icon. Japanese Gulch, a 100-acre urban forest, runs through the middle of town. Harbour Pointe, the master-planned community on the south end, has its own golf course and commercial center. Boeing\'s Paine Field operations border the city to the east.',
